Auto-mapdump at end of level generation (017-auto-mapdump patch).

When NETHACK_MAPDUMP_DIR env var is set, writes a compact dump file for each
generated level after level_finalize_topology(), and emits ^mapdump[id] to the
RNG log via event_log().

Changes:
  include/extern.h: declare harness_auto_mapdump()
  src/mklev.c:      call harness_auto_mapdump() in mklev() after level_finalize_topology()
  src/mklev.c:      add harness_auto_mapdump() function at end of file

--- a/include/extern.h
+++ b/include/extern.h
@@ -1571,6 +1571,7 @@ extern void level_finalize_topology(void);
 extern void mklev(void);
+extern void harness_auto_mapdump(void);
 #ifdef SPECIALIZATION

--- a/src/mklev.c
+++ b/src/mklev.c
@@ -1585,6 +1585,8 @@ mklev(void)

     level_finalize_topology();

+    harness_auto_mapdump();
+
     reseed_random(rn2);

(harness_auto_mapdump function appended at end of mklev.c)

Compact file format:
  T<rle-grid>   terrain types (levl[x][y].typ)
  F<rle-grid>   5-bit flags
  H<rle-grid>   horizontal bit
  L<rle-grid>   lit bit
  R<rle-grid>   6-bit roomno
  O<x>,<y>,<otyp>,<quan>;...   objects
  M<x>,<y>,<mndx>,<mhp>;...   monsters
  K<x>,<y>,<ttyp>;...          traps

Grid encoding: each row is chars, runs of 3+ compressed as ~<count>,<char>
(tilde prefix + comma separator prevents ambiguity with digit cell values),
rows separated by '|'. Cell encoding: 0-9->'0'-'9', 10-35->'a'-'z', 36-61->'A'-'Z'.
